==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flower-fence
<hw>Flow"er-fence`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A tropical leguminous bush (<spn>Poinciana pulcherrima</spn>,
<it>or</it> <spn>C⟦ae⟧salpinia, pulcherrima</spn>) with prickly
branches, and showy yellow or red flowers; -- so named from its having
been sometimes used for hedges in the West Indies.</def>
<rj><au>Baird.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flowerful</ent>⟦br⟧
